# AEGIS — Docker build context filter
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This file is consulted by `docker build` from the repo root. Anything
# matched here never enters the build context, which keeps:
#   1. secrets out of layers, even if a misplaced COPY would pick them up,
#   2. the build context small (faster uploads to remote builders),
#   3. cache invalidation predictable (editing a README doesn't bust deps).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- VCS, editor, OS noise ------------------------------------------------
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.editorconfig
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo

# --- Secrets (defense in depth — they must not be in the repo anyway) -----
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
*.p12
*.pfx
.aws/
.gcp/
*.enc

# --- Node / pnpm artifacts ------------------------------------------------
**/node_modules
**/.pnpm-store
**/.pnpm-debug.log
**/npm-debug.log*
**/yarn-debug.log*
**/yarn-error.log*

# --- Build outputs --------------------------------------------------------
**/dist
**/build
**/out
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/.cache
**/.parcel-cache
**/coverage
**/.nyc_output

# --- Test fixtures + reports ----------------------------------------------
**/__snapshots__
**/test-results
**/playwright-report
**/junit.xml

# --- CI / docs / meta -----------------------------------------------------
.github
.changeset
docs
*.md
!apps/api/README.md
LICENSE

# --- Docker meta (we don't need our own dockerfiles inside the image) ----
Dockerfile*
.dockerignore
docker-compose*.yml
infra/docker/

# --- Local DB / Redis volumes (in case someone bind-mounts them) ----------
**/aegis_pg_data
**/aegis_redis_data
**/postgres-data
**/redis-data

# --- Misc -----------------------------------------------------------------
*.log
*.tsbuildinfo
.eslintcache
